726409f-c.title: Queens: Corona Avenue - 56th Avenue
726409f-c.text:
Corona Avenue, east side, at 56th Avenue, viewing south-
ward, showing dwellings on both corners of the street which
have been converted into tourist accomodations for visitors
to the New York World's Fair of 1939-40. View 3 shows the
S.E. corner of the two thoroughfares.
June 23, 1940
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
